      "content": "When interacting with East Asians, it's best to avoid direct eye contact, as this can be perceived as aggressive or confrontational. Also, refrain from using gestures that imply a sense of urgency or excitement, such as tapping your foot or using open palm gestures, as these can be seen as impolite. In West Africa, it's best to avoid physical displays of affection, such as hugging or kissing, as these can be seen as overly familiar or even insulting. Additionally, avoid eating with your left hand, as this is considered unclean in many African cultures. When it comes to fashion, avoid brightly colored or patterned clothing, as these can be seen as tacky or attention-seeking. Instead, opt for neutral colors like navy, black, or gray, and avoid any clothing with cultural or symbolic significance that may be misinterpreted.",
